{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_adamsmorgan_ver01/data/sn84026749/00222254668/1929121801/1211.xml":{"full_text":"20\nHIGHWftr BUILT\nFOB SPEED IS\nURGED\n5 \u201cSpeed is a fact in modem traf\nfic; there remains the necessity\nof making it safe.\" H. H. Frank\nlin, president of the Franklin Au\ntomobile Company told the Na\ntional Safety Council in urging\nthat it direct its efforts toward\nproviding roads that are safe for\nautomobile travel at high rates\nof speed.\nFranklin indorsed the declara\ntion to the council by Paul C.\nHoffman, vice president of the\nStudebaker Corporation, that re\nmoval of maximum speed limits\nby States would save lives. Hoff\nfrian pointed out that the slow\ndriver who blocks the normal\nflow .of traffic Is the greatest\nmenace on the highway.\nThis also is in line with the\nstatement of C. F. Kettering, di\nrector of the research laboratories\nOs the General Motors Corpora\ntion, that the' solution of the\ntraffic problems lies in making\nsustained speeds of M to TO miles\nan hour possible over long dis\ntances.\n\u201cThe right kind of roads will\nmake fast travel by automobile\nsafer than the slower travel of\ntoday and safety authorities must\nconcern themselves with this fea\nture of the problem,\u201d Franklin\nsaid. \"Mr. Hoffman\u2019s remarks\nwere timely and he chose the\nproper place to make them,\nnamely, before the' National\nSafety Council.\u201d\nCars of today are faster than\never before and the next few\nyears will see machines Capable\nof speeds in excess of 100 miles\nan hour with Safety, Franklin\nsaid. Modem highways will make\nmotoring at these high speeds\nfar safer than driving is today.\nTwo-way goads, cross roads, rail\nroad grade crossings, curves,\nsmall villages and towns slow\nup traffic and offer most of the\nhasards of present day driving,\nMr. Franklin contends.\nmm\nDUE IN SPRING\nDETROIT, Dec. IT.\u2014The ban\ntam Austin, a small car of dis\ntinctive smartness, unique in size,\nweight and performance, will join\nthe fashion parade oh American\nroads this spring, according to C.\nA. Best, general sales manager of\nthe American Austin Car Com\npany here. This announcement\nfollows the news that the bantam\nAustin will go into production\nin February at the Butler (Pa.)\nplant of the company.\nBigger and Better\nTo Serve You\np' X/ ft?'?WMI^'\"\"\"HL? x StSw\nI. /wi lb\nWo have just added 25,000 additional square feet of bright, clean\nwork rooms to our original building. You will find all the newest\nshop equipment and skilled mechanics who have received their\ntraining at the Ford Factory School.\nOur policy of honest fair dealing, and good service has been\nresponsible for our growth and success.\nThis BIGGER and BETTER plant is for servicing Ford Cars only!\nYou Are Cordially Invited to Inspect Our New Plant\nTRIANGLE MOTOR CO.\nAuthorized Dealers\n_ NEW YORK AVE. AT NORTH CAPITOL ST.\nbpm Daily T AM. to t PM.<\u2014Smi*y t AM. to S PM.\nHaynes Booster of Good Roads Bill\nLeft to Right-\u2014Representative C. C. Dowell, of lowa, who introduced a bill to increase\nthe Federal good-roads appropriation 150,000,000; Frederick Haynes, president of Du\nrant Motors and a director of the United States Chamber of Commerce, who appeared\nbefore the good\u00abroads committee to urge the immediate passage of this bill, which\nwill make the yearly expenditure for good roads >125,000,000.\nHaynes Sees Hoover\nAiding Prosperity\nBy J. LIO BUGRUI\nThe United Stales is the most*\nprosperous country in the world.'\nstated Frederick Haynes, presi\ndent of Durant Motor* and a\ndirector In the United States\nChamber of Commerce. Mr\nHaynes, while here attending a\nFederal Roads Committee meet\ning, expressed optimism and con\nfidence in the future of America.\nMr. Haynes lauded President\nHoover for displaying the wis\ndom in marshaling the wealth\nof the country to combat the pes\nsimism caused by the recent stock\nmarket crash.\n\u201cWhite a member of this con\nference I was inspired by the\nbusiness leadership ability of our\nPresident and the speedy ac\nceptance nt President Hoover\u2019s\nsuggestion to create more \u201cwork\"\nby the nation\u2019s business and in-,\ndustrial leaders is overpowering\ntestimony of their confidence in\nthe future, continued Mr. Haynes.\n\u201cConfidence, enthusiasm and\naggressivei ess must be the foun*\nelation fbi every forward move\nment and I am confident the\nbillions of dollars that will be\nspent wisely in building through\nout the nation will stimulate our\nfuture prex.-perity.\n\u201cBetter roads win tend toward\nTHE WASHINGTON TIMSES\n\u25baincreasing our prosperity and\nwhile America has over one half\nof the world's highways, there\nare still future Improvements and\nI am here in behalf of the Dowell\nbiU and an urging Congress to\nimmediately pass this so as to\nincrease the Federal good roads\nappropriation from $75,000,000\nannually to $121,000,000.\nThe automobile business is In\na very healthy condition and di\nrectly and indirectly employ* over\n4,000,000 persons, factories ate\nrunning now at full production,\nworking on new models, and\ndealers and manufacturers in 1030\nwin enjoy their most prosperous\nyear.\nThe automobile year of 1930\nwill be prosperous due to the\nenormous replacement and export\nmarket, and three will be approx\nimately 4,000,000 units for local\nmarkets built, and over 1,000,000\nfor export, stated Haynes.\nJanuary, February and March\nwill not be record-breaking months.\nThe year will start off conserva\ntively, and will not equal 1929,\nbut production and sales will\ngather momentum, and the re\nmaining month* will surpass the\nlast nine months of this year.\nNash Models Increased\nS2O to $l4O January 1\nKENO6HA, Wls., Dec. 18.\u2014In\ncreased prices effective January\n1 are announced by C. W. Nash,\npresident of the Nash Motors\nCompany. Increases range from\nS3O to $l4O per model, and cover\naU three series, Single Six, Twin-\nIgnition Six and Twin-Ignition\nEight..\n\u25a0'Sr\ni\ni IfflJ\nrCI\nufiliiliftiW'xs\"ill l if\n'H DO THE IMPORTANT PART OF YOUR\nI\" CHRISTMAS SHOPPING HERE I\nrOR the one gift which is more important than all the rest,\nI the one place to go to get it is the Nash showroom. If only\nthe best IS good enough \u2014if only the finest Will do \u2014the car New\u00dfodyDe*lgns\u2014UngWhe\u00ablba\u00abet\u2014Radlatortwhlt\u00dfulfr-ln\nyOU Can choose and know you are right, IS the 193\u00ae Nash \u2014S\u00ab|f^narelxln^Cabla^Ach>at\u00bbd4-Whaal\u00dfrolca*\u2014(WlPaad\nThe Twin-Ignition Eight, the Twin-Ignition Six and\nthe Single Six all bring to motoring new features not found c\u00aev\u00bbrs, wmi umiwk LubricaHon\u2014world\u2019s\nrm Inns\nI g %a #1 wiwiiwf vi 1 n\u2022s 1 urifwti 1 r wfvwi irt*v\u00abc\u00abTvd YiOO*\nin other cars which compare in price, when you drive one board and dmh\u2014 and these additional features in\nyou will know instantly that there is new enjoyment to be had A\nfrom motoring. You will also know that, for the one most itn- covnf.rw.i S hwd, Hoiiow CranWn*-Afeminm\nff Connecting Rod*\u2014\u2018Stoonng Shock Hunlnotor\u2014\u201cA\u00df wmdowA\nportant gift/your shopping is finished\u2014a 1930 Nash' 400 I ww\u00abhoWa Dupim* Non-shaMorabfo Moto oia**.\nM\nTWIN-IGNITION EIGHT TWIN-IGNITION SIX SINGLE SIX\nFMCIOf*OMSIttSTOSIMOUe.b.feMew) PMC\u00bb MOM SIM TO SI\u00abM (Le.b.taM'rt R*Ob FROM Wls TO SIRS Ue.kfaweM\nLow Down Piyrngnt and Convtnient Extended Tarm* ll Poked\nWALLACE MOTOR COMPANY Distributor\nRetail Salesrooms 1709 L Street N.> W. Decatur 2280\nASSOCIATE MALEKS\nROBERT J. NASH MOTOR CO. HALL KERR MOTOR CO. HAWKINS-NASH MOTOR CO. POTTER NASH CO. PATTERSON-NASH MOTORS\n1415 Irving St N. W. 131 BStS. E. 1529 14th Street N. W. Decatur 3320 Silver Spring, Md. 3UO MStN. W.\n4/- BIRVON-NABH MOTOR CO., 050 Wilwn B&evard, Clarendon, Va.\nThe Ifatlonut Dotty\nBUICK PRICES\nIDYINCE\nr> L\nBuick and Marquette price*\nhave been Increased, ranging from\n$25 to $75 being a return to about\nthe same list price* on several\nmodels which prevailed during the\npast year, while on some models\nthe new prices are still lower than\nthe past year.\nThe above statement is made\nby B. T. Strong, president of the\nBuick Motor Company. Comment\ning upon the readjustment* of\nlist prices, Strong says that \u201cthese\nadjustments are necessary to con\nform with the increased costs in\nproducing\u00abour present line of\nquality autombbltes recently Intro\nduced and so wonderfully re\nceived by the public.\n\u201cIt has been the policy of the\nBuick Motor Company to build a\nproduct truly accepted by all as\na standard of comparison, which\nnecessitates at all times the\nquality of our product being main\ntained.\nChristmas Buyers Hail\nCut in Income Taxes\nChristmas shoppers can spend\nwith a freer hand this Christmas\nsecure in the knowledge that the\nGovernment isn\u2019t going to take\nso much of their money in in\ncome taxes.\nPresident Hoover\u2019s signature to\nthe tax reduction resolution auto\nmatically gives the income tax\npaying public about $190,000,000,\nwhich would have been due next\nMarch.\nThe new tax law, which is only\nof one year's duration, cuts in\ncome taxes to the \u201clittle fellow\"\nof below $5,000 net Income almost\nto the vanishing point.\n\nWEDNESDAY, DECEMBER 18,\nAttention to Details\nCuts Down Fuel\nDETROIT, Dec. 18.\u2014MUlions,\nof dollars could be saved annually\nby the automobile-owning public\nthrough a more strict observance\nof the factors that control the\ngasoline mileage offered by the\naverage automobile, It was re\nvealed in a survey on fuel econ\nomy completed today by the Chev\nrolet Motor Company.\nA gain of from two to five mites\non the gallon of gas could be af\nfected, on the average, it was\nshown, if the motorists paid strict\nattention to the elements that\ngovern fuel consumption.\nJust how this attention to fuel\neconomy brings its reward is illus\ntrated in records of performances\ncoming in the company\u2019s offices,\nwhich show that although the\nChevrolet Bix is expected to run\napproximately 20 miles to the gal\nlon, motorists in various sections\nof the country are getting 23, 24\nand 25 miles through just a little\nadded attention to the matter.\nChief Factors\nThe majority of item* to be\nwatched are rather obvious to the\naverage automobile owner, but\nthrough an inadequate apprecia\ntion of their importance, are com\nmonly overlooked.\nThe survey seta down specifi\ncally a number of factors, which,\nif observed, should increase your\nmileage two to five mile* to the\ngallon.\nThey are:\nWhen starfding or waiting for\nthe light to change, don\u2019t race\nyour motor.\nWhen you are to make a stop\nof more than a minute, turn off\nyour motor.\nDon\u2019t drive at excessive speeds\nunless the occasion demands.\nHigh-speed traveling bums more\ngas.\nRemember that the faster you\ndrive the more gas you consume.\n\n1\n>Bo, when you find that you are\nabout out of gas and are heading\nfor a gas-station, take it slowly\nand your chances for negotiating\nthe distance will be greater.\nWhen starting watch the\nchoke. Don\u2019t drive with the\nchoke out a moment mors than\nnecessary.\nBrakes Impsrtaat\nBe sure your brakes are not\ndragging. This cuts down your\nmileage. Get your brakes in\nspected frequently.\nHave your valves ground when\nthey need it.\nSee that the idling adjustment\non your carburetor is set at the\nproper point so that the mixture\nis not too rich. If it is not at\nthe proper point it gives you\ninefficient idling performance\nand wastes gas.\nDon\u2019t fill your tank full to the\ncap, some will escape through\nthe vent in the cap.\nDon\u2019t ride the clutch.\nWatch gas line for leaks at\nJoints. Check it periodically to\nsee that fittings are tight.\nBe sure that spark is in fully\nadvanced position.\nAvoid excessive use of brakes\nin traffic.\nObservance <rf these sugges\ntions, the survey points out, will\nsave.m<mey for the motorist and\nadd considerable miteage to\nyour driving and reduce the num\nber of necessary stop* at the\ngasoline station.\nSpanish Cruiser Speeds\n35 Miles in Trial Trip\nFERROL,Spain,Dec. It (LNB.).\nThe new Spanish cruiser, Miguel\nCervanves, aevciopea speea oi\n35 miles an hour in a trial here\nyesterday.\nIt Is reported the vessel will\nshortly nuke a trip to the Argen\ntine.\nOIKLANfI PLANS\nSALES WEEK\nOne hundred and fifty Oak\nland-Pontiac deafen of the Wash\nington sone staged a meeting this\nweek at the Mayflower Hotel to\ndiscuss with factory officials sell\ning plans for 1930. Ths meeting\nwas called by Zone Manager K.\nL. Camp and was conducted by\nW. B. Sawyer, assistant general\nsates manager of Oakland Motor\nCar Company.\nBeside the usual discussion of\nthe company's two products, the\nOakland and the Pontiac car,**\nplans were made for a series of\nspecial demonstrations.\nOutlook Good\nSawyer was optimistic over the\nbusiness outlook for next year.\nIn addressing the dealers, ho\nsaid:\n\u201cIn approaching our sales pro\ngram for next year, we have\nevery reason to believe that 1930\nwill be a good year for business.\nBusiness authorities assure us\nthat general conditions are sound,\nindustry and gO'touliniw are In a\nhealthy position and there is no\nreason to fear a depression.\nBo Bash\n\"We are not making any rash\npredictions regarding Increases in\nautomobile sates next year, but\nintend to build according to the\nretail demand as reflected by our\ndealers* forecasts. There will be\nno crowding or forcing of cars on\nour dealers except as they them\nselves order more cars than they\ncan actually use.\n\"However, since we realise that\nour sates will be limited only by\nthe retail sales, we ourselves ex\npect to given yqu more help than\nwe have ever given in the past in\nthe actual soliciting and promo\ntion of retail sates.\"","height":"30414","width":"24194"}}
